Overall Progress
Day 101 showed noticeable improvement with the new weekly conversational phrases introduced on Day 100. Most of the difficulty shifted away from remembering vocabulary and toward polishing small grammar details such as word order, articles, and verb forms. Pimsleur Lesson 12 is now well retained, and longer conversational sentences are beginning to feel more automatic. Compared with only a few weeks ago, you’re producing complete thoughts with less hesitation and relying less on direct English translation. Your confidence with travel conversations continues to grow, providing a strong foundation as you prepare for future trips to Colombia and other Spanish-speaking countries.
